/* STDLIB/iii/aether/iii_studio.iii -- III STUDIO: the sovereign exact-mathematics IDE.  ONE window (ui_win), ONE
 * [APP-SURFACE-MODULE] -- window/app execution surface: compiled by its family gate so it cannot rot;
 * its unreached exports are app-class BY NATURE (headless corpus cannot pump a window) and are excluded
 * from the v3 dark census (mechanism: sanctus/corpus_coverage, reunification W0.2).
 * 1280x800 framebuffer, ONE visual identity (studio_theme), SIX live workspaces -- each a real instrument wired
 * to the real system, none decorative:
 *   HOME    -- the system's own numbers + a launcher that spawns real sibling binaries
 *   FORGE   -- edit a real .iii file and COMPILE it with the real iiis-2 (real stderr, real exit code)
 *   BENCH   -- the exact-physics workbench (integer + Sqrt-sum verdicts, live)
 *   LENS    -- the gated exact ray-cast renderer, orbited live
 *   RENDER  -- the ONE unified exact renderer: 1D spectrum / 2D field / 3D ray-cast, in colour, over TIME, sealed to .ixr
 *   STOMA   -- the sovereign shell as centerpiece: real verbs, real spawn, journaled (the terminal Stoma, windowed)
 * The shell owns routing only: workspaces own their state; the theme owns the look; the substrate owns the OS.
 * Everything on screen is drawn by III's own rasterizer and fonts.  F1..F6 or click the rail; ESC quits. */
module iii_studio

